    <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">How to Find SNGPL Consumer Number — Where is it on Your Bill?</h1>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-4 rounded-lg mb-8">
      <p class="font-semibold text-primary-800">Quick Answer: The SNGPL consumer number is a <strong>10-digit number</strong> on the <strong>top-left of your bill</strong> labeled <strong>"Consumer No."</strong> or <strong>"Account No."</strong> — just below your name and address. It contains only digits, no letters.</p>
    </div>

    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">To check your <strong>Sui Northern Gas Pipelines (SNGPL)</strong> gas bill online — whether you live in Lahore, Islamabad, Rawalpindi, Faisalabad, Multan, Peshawar, or any other city in Punjab, KP, or AJK — you need your 10-digit consumer number. SNGPL uses the term "Consumer Number" (sometimes called "Account Number") instead of the "Reference Number" used by electricity DISCOs, but the purpose is the same: it's the unique identifier that lets any bill-checking service retrieve your account from SNGPL's database. The consumer number never changes for your connection, so once you've found it on any previous bill, you can use it forever. This guide shows exactly where on the bill to find it, what the number looks like, and how to recover it if you've lost all your old bills.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What is SNGPL and Where Does It Operate?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">SNGPL is Pakistan's largest natural gas utility, serving over <strong>7.4 million consumers</strong> across northern and central Pakistan. The company was incorporated in 1963 and is headquartered in Lahore. Its license area covers the entire provinces of <strong>Punjab</strong> and <strong>Khyber Pakhtunkhwa (KP)</strong>, plus <strong>Azad Kashmir (AJK)</strong> and the <strong>Islamabad Capital Territory</strong>. SSGC (Sui Southern Gas Company) handles the rest of Pakistan — Sindh and Balochistan. Major cities served by SNGPL include:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Punjab:</strong> Lahore, Rawalpindi, Faisalabad, Multan, Gujranwala, Sialkot, Sargodha, Bahawalpur, Sahiwal, Gujrat</li>
      <li><strong>KP:</strong> Peshawar, Mardan, Abbottabad, Charsadda, Nowshera, Kohat, Bannu</li>
      <li><strong>AJK:</strong> Muzaffarabad, Mirpur, Rawalakot</li>
      <li><strong>ICT:</strong> Islamabad, Bhara Kahu, Tarnol</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">If your gas connection is in any of these areas, SNGPL is your supplier. SSGC handles Sindh and Balochistan — they are completely separate companies with separate consumer databases, so make sure you check your bill on the right checker.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Where Exactly is the SNGPL Consumer Number?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Unlike electricity bills (which put the reference number on the top-right), SNGPL gas bills put the consumer number on the <strong>top-left</strong> of the bill — just below your name and address. Look for a number labeled <strong>"Consumer No."</strong> or <strong>"Account No."</strong> printed in bold.</p>

    <div class="bg-neutral-900 text-green-400 font-mono rounded-xl p-5 mb-6 text-sm overflow-x-auto">
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-xs mb-2">// SNGPL Bill — Top Left Section</p>
      <p>┌─────────────────────────────────┐</p>
      <p>│  Sui Northern Gas Pipelines Bill   │</p>
      <p>│  Consumer Name: [Your Name]      │</p>
      <p>│  Address: [Your Address]         │</p>
      <p class="text-yellow-300">│  <strong>Consumer No: 0123456789</strong>      │ ← Here!</p>
      <p>│  Tariff: Domestic (R)            │</p>
      <p>│  Sanctioned Load: 0.5 HM³/month │</p>
      <p>│  Meter Number: 12345678          │</p>
      <p>│  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │</p>
      <p>│  │ Reading: 1245 HM³        │   │</p>
      <p>│  │ Consumption: 65 HM³      │   │</p>
      <p>│  │ Total Payable: Rs. 5,210 │   │</p>
      <p>│  └──────────────────────────┘   │</p>
      <p>│  [████████ BARCODE ████████]    │</p>
      <p>└─────────────────────────────────┘</p>
    </div>

    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">The consumer number is printed in <strong>bold, slightly larger font</strong> than the surrounding text. Position is identical on every SNGPL bill — old bills from years ago will have it in the same spot.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What Does the SNGPL Consumer Number Look Like?</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Always exactly <strong>10 digits</strong> — never more, never less</li>
      <li>Only numbers — no letters (A, B, C) or dashes</li>
      <li>Example: <code class="bg-neutral-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded font-mono">0123456789</code></li>
      <li>Printed in <strong>bold</strong> near the top-left of your bill</li>
      <li>Labeled <strong>"Consumer No."</strong> or <strong>"Account No."</strong></li>
      <li>Stays the same every month (only changes if connection is re-registered)</li>
      <li>SNGPL consumer numbers typically begin with digits 2–9 (regional prefix)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Can't Find Your SNGPL Consumer Number?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">If you've lost all previous bills, here are the recovery options:</p>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-8">
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-1">1. Check any old bill</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Your consumer number never changes. Any previous SNGPL bill — even one from years ago — has the same consumer number. Ask family, neighbors, or your landlord if they have an old bill from your connection.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-1">2. Call SNGPL helpline 1199</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Provide your CNIC number, full name, and address. The customer service representative can retrieve your consumer number after verifying your identity. Helpline operates 24/7.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-1">3. Visit any SNGPL customer service center</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Bring your CNIC and proof of residence. SNGPL customer service centers exist in Lahore (HQ, 16-Km Ferozepur Road), Islamabad, Rawalpindi, Faisalabad, Multan, Gujranwala, Sialkot, Sargodha, Bahawalpur, Peshawar, Mardan, and Abbottabad.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-1">4. Check your mobile wallet payment history</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">If you've ever paid your SNGPL bill via JazzCash, EasyPaisa, or a bank app, the consumer number is saved in your payment history. Open the app → Payment History → look for past gas bill payments.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-1">5. Use the SNGPL online portal</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Visit sngpl.com.pk → "Customer Services" → "Forgot Consumer Number". Enter your CNIC and registered phone number to retrieve the consumer number via SMS.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">SNGPL Consumer Number vs Meter Number</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">SNGPL bills display two different identifiers. Knowing the difference helps when checking bills and filing complaints:</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg">
        <thead class="bg-neutral-100">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Feature</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Consumer Number</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Meter Number</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-neutral-200">
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Length</td><td class="p-3">10 digits</td><td class="p-3">8 digits (sometimes with letters)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Position on bill</td><td class="p-3">Top-left (below address)</td><td class="p-3">Middle-right section</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Changes over time?</td><td class="p-3">Only if re-registered</td><td class="p-3">Yes, if meter replaced</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Used for</td><td class="p-3">Online bill check, payment</td><td class="p-3">Meter identification only</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Works on our checker?</td><td class="p-3">Yes</td><td class="p-3">No</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Accepted at banks?</td><td class="p-3">Yes</td><td class="p-3">No</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Common Mistakes When Entering the Consumer Number</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Missing leading zero:</strong> When copy-pasting, the first "0" often gets cut off. Always count the digits — must be exactly 10.</li>
      <li><strong>Entering the meter number by mistake:</strong> Meter number is shorter (usually 8 digits) and identifies the physical meter, not your billing account.</li>
      <li><strong>Confusing SNGPL with SSGC:</strong> SNGPL covers Punjab, KP, AJK, and Islamabad. SSGC covers Sindh and Balochistan. If you live in Karachi or Quetta, your gas bill is SSGC, not SNGPL.</li>
      <li><strong>Entering dashes or spaces:</strong> The system rejects special characters. Enter 10 digits without any separators.</li>
      <li><strong>Using an old SNGPL consumer number after meter replacement:</strong> The consumer number stays the same even after meter replacement, but verify with SNGPL if you've recently had a meter change.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-10">
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Where is the consumer number on SNGPL bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">The SNGPL consumer number is a 10-digit number printed in bold on the top-left section of your Sui Northern Gas bill, labeled 'Consumer No.' or 'Account No.'. It is different from your gas meter number and stays the same every month.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What is the SNGPL consumer number format?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">The SNGPL consumer number is always exactly 10 digits. No letters, no spaces, no dashes. Example format: 0123456789. It stays the same every month and is unique to your gas connection.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to check SNGPL bill without consumer number?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">If you don't have your SNGPL consumer number, call SNGPL helpline 1199 with your CNIC. You can also visit any SNGPL customer service center with your CNIC and proof of residence.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Is SNGPL consumer number the same as gas meter number?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">No. SNGPL consumer number is 10 digits and identifies your billing account. Gas meter number is a separate identifier (usually 8 digits, sometimes with letters) printed elsewhere on the bill and identifies the physical meter installed at your premises.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Which provinces does SNGPL cover?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">SNGPL covers Punjab, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa (KP), Azad Kashmir (AJK), and Islamabad Capital Territory. Major cities include Lahore, Islamabad, Rawalpindi, Faisalabad, Multan, Peshawar, Gujranwala, Sialkot, and Bahawalpur. SSGC handles Sindh and Balochistan.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">I live in Karachi — can I use SNGPL consumer number?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">No. SNGPL only serves northern Pakistan (Punjab, KP, AJK, Islamabad). If you live in Karachi, Hyderabad, Sukkur, Quetta, or any city in Sindh/Balochistan, your gas supplier is SSGC. Use our SSGC bill checker for that.</div></details>
    </div>

